ics in the early years of the international women's movement|url=http://scholar.harvard.edu/files/kristenghodsee/files/un_decade_reflections.pdf|journal=[[Women's Studies International Forum]]|date=2010|volume=33|pages=3–12|doi=10.1016/j.wsif.2009.11.008|accessdate=7 May 2017|publisher=Elsevier|location=Amsterdam, the Netherlands|issn=0277-5395}} *{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Olcott|first=Jocelyn|title=International Women's Year: The Greatest Consciousness-Raising Event in History|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5zslDwAAQBAJ|year=2017|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=New York, NY|isbn=978-0-674-46885-6}} *{{cite book|ref=harv|last1=Pierson|first1=Ruth Roach|last2=Cohen|first2=Marjorie Griffin|title=Canadian Women's Issues: Volume II: Bold Visions|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KLWu5TNmw8sC&pg=PA362|year=1993|publisher=James Lorimer & Company|location=Toronto, Canada|doi=10.1093/oso/9780195327687.001.0001}} *{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Pietilä|first=Hilkka|title=The Unfinished Story of Women and the United Nations|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tpsg3xsQv8cC&pg=PA42|year=2007|publisher=UN Non-Governmental Liaison Service|location=New York, New York|id=GGKEY:K1H1G5PGUBB}} *{{cite news|ref=harv|last1=Teltsch|first1=Kathleen|title=U.N. Wants It to Be More Than a 'Ladies’ Meeting'|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1974/05/10/archives/un-wants-it-to-be-more-than-a-ladies-meeting.html?_r=0|accessdate=8 May 2017|publisher=''[[The New York Times]]''|date=10 May 1974|location=New York City, New York|page=43}} *{{cite report|ref={{harvid|"Background of the Conference"|1976}}|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|title=Report of the World Conference of the International Women’s Year: Mexico City 19 June-2 July 1975|url=https://www.un.org/womenwatch/daw/beijing/otherconferences/Mexico/Mexico%20section%20IV%20-%20VIII.pdf|chapter=Part II: Background of the Conference|publisher=United Nations|accessdate=8 May 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/2017