'''Joseph Kaven''' [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] is a [[Papua New Guinea]]n [[physician]] who works at Nonga Base Hospital, [[Rabaul]], [[East New Britain]].<ref>[http://www.ajtmh.org/cgi/content/abstract/31/4/822 "Severe Staphylococcal Pneumonia Complicating Pyomyositis"], Euan M. Scrimgeour & Joseph Kaven, ''American Society of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene'', 31(4), 1982, pp. 822-826</ref> <ref>[http://www.postcourier.com.pg/20030505/news09 "Possible case looms in ENB"], ''Post Courier'', May 5, 2003</ref> He has worked on improving health service access to rural areas of Papua New Guinea.<ref>[https://archive.is/20070625060547/http://www.thenational.com.pg/102907/Nation%2025.htm "Medical society holds symposium in ENB"], Veronica Manuk, ''The National'', October 29, 2007</ref>

Kaven was appointed [[Commander of the Order of the British Empire]] (CBE) in the 2009 Birthday Honours for "service to health and medical research, particularly in infectious disease control".<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=59093 |date=13 June 2009 |page=2 |supp=y }}</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2009/jun/13/queens-birthday-honours-list-commonwealth "Queen's birthday honours list: Commonwealth"], ''The Guardian'', June 13, 2009</ref>

