{{Expand Lithuanian|date=October 2016|Juras Požela (1982)}} {{Infobox politician | image = Juras-pozela-1982.jpg | image_size = | caption = Juras Požela | honorific-prefix = | name = Juras Požela | honorific-suffix = | office = [[Ministry of Health (Lithuania)|Minister of Health]] of Lithuania | term_start = 15 March 2016 | term_end = 16 October 2016 | predecessor = [[Rimantė Šalaševičiūtė]] | successor = {{ill|Aurelijus Veryga|lt}} | birth_date = 12 April 1982 | birth_place = [[Vilnius]], Lithuania | death_date = 16 October 2016 (aged 34) | death_place = Vilnius, Lithuania | party = [[Social Democratic Party of Lithuania|LSDP]] (2000{{ndash}}2016) | alma_mater = [[Vilnius University]] | occupation = Politician | religion = | signature = | footnotes = }}
'''Juras Požela''' (12 April 1982 – 16 October 2016) was a Lithuanian politician who served as the [[Ministry of Health (Lithuania)|Minister of Health]] of Lithuania from March 2016 until his death on 16 October 2016 from [[pancreatitis]].<ref>[http://lietuvosdiena.lrytas.lt/nelaimes/mire-sveikatos-apsaugos-ministras-juras-pozela.htm Mirė sveikatos apsaugos ministras Juras Požela] (in Lithuanian)</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.baltictimes.com/lithuania_s_healthmin_pozela_passes_away/|title=Lithuania's HealthMin Pozela passes away|date=16 October 2016|publisher=The Baltic Times|accessdate=16 October 2016}}</ref> He was also a [[Seimas]] member, Youth and Sports Affairs Committee Chairman and a presidium member of the [[Social Democratic Party of Lithuania]].
