{{Infobox National Paralympic Committee | title = Zimbabwe National Paralympic Committee | logo = | size = | country = Zimbabwe | code = ZIM | created = 2010 | recognized = | association = | headquarters = | president = [[Michael Ityaishe Bulagango]]<ref name="board">[http://www.zimparalympic.org/about-us/board-members/ "About us: Board members"], ZNPC</ref> | secretary general = [[Lewis Garaba]]<ref name="board" /> | website = [http://www.zimparalympic.org/ www.zimparalympic.org] }} The '''Zimbabwe National Paralympic Committee''' (ZNPC) is responsible for [[Zimbabwe]]'s participation in the [[Paralympic Games]], and for overseeing disability sports in the country. Its mission it to support athletes with disabilities "competing at both the grassroots and elite levels".<ref>[http://www.zimparalympic.org/ ZNPC homepage]</ref>
The Zimbabwe National Paralympic Committee was only officially launched and registered in 2010. Prior to this, "the government provided financial aid during the Paralympic Games, [but] there was no co-ordinated mechanism to maintain athletes' momentum between the Games", and athletes "had to find their own sponsor, coach and manager who would finance the training, travelling and their participation at competitions".<ref>[http://www.zimparalympic.org/about-us/history/ "About us: History"], ZNPC</ref>
